[It is not clearly stated what the time line of the cases was here, which would be useful in determining whether the food handler was the source of the other cases. This is another reminder that, in the same way that healthcare workers are vaccinated against certain diseases to help protect their patients, food handlers should be vaccinated against HAV to protect the public. Since HAV is heat labile, pizza is not a common vehicle unless some ingredients, such as salad, are added after cooking. - Mod.LL

